# StyleUp Backend — Project Context

**Stack:** NestJS 10, MongoDB/Mongoose 8, Redis (ioredis 5), JWT auth, Razorpay payments, pnpm 10.
**Domain:** Barber/beauty booking marketplace, Kerala, India. Hexagonal/ports-adapters architecture.

## Directory Layout

```
src/
├── modules/    # Feature modules: auth, users, providers, bookings, payments, notifications
├── common/     # Decorators, guards, filters, interceptors, pipes, middlewares
├── infra/      # External adapters — database.module, redis.module
├── config/     # Env validation (Joi), typed configuration loader
├── health/     # Terminus health checks (Mongo + Redis)
└── shared/     # Shared types and interfaces
```

## Run Commands

```bash
pnpm run build   # TypeScript compile — run after every substantive change
pnpm run lint    # ESLint + Prettier — run before finishing any task
```

## TypeScript — Zero `any` Policy

`any` is forbidden everywhere. Use `unknown` and narrow with type guards or `in` checks.

```typescript
// BAD
function handle(data: any) { return data.id; }

// GOOD
function handle(data: unknown): string {
  if (typeof data === 'object' && data !== null && 'id' in data) {
    return String((data as Record<string, unknown>).id);
  }
  throw new Error('Invalid payload');
}
```

## File Naming

| Artifact | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Module/Controller/Service | kebab-case | `bookings.service.ts` |
| DTO | `create-x.dto.ts`, `x-response.dto.ts` | `create-booking.dto.ts` |
| Schema | `x.schema.ts` | `booking.schema.ts` |
| Barrel | `index.ts` | — |

Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`. No hardcoded secrets or connection strings.

## Scope Lock

- Do not add npm packages without flagging first.
- Do not change module structure or folder layout without explicit instruction.
- Do not write feature/business logic when the task is scoped as "setup" or "scaffolding."
